      "side": 1,
      "message": "The creation guard fires for **any non-IANA field**, including `PLDM_FRU_FIELD_TYPE_VENDOR`, `PLDM_FRU_FIELD_TYPE_CHASSIS`, etc... — all of which hit `break` in the switch and set **no** D-Bus properties.\n\nIn a scenario where a terminus has only these unhandled fields, we would still get empty decorator interfaces registered on D-Bus. \n\nI would suggest move the creation guard inside only the cases that actually set a property in the form of a helper function that initializes the decorator interface only if it doesn\u0027t already exist.\n\nSomething like\n\n```\n\t\tcase PLDM_FRU_FIELD_TYPE_MODEL:\n\t\t\tinitFruDecoratorIfNotExist();\n\t\t\tfruDecoratorsIntf-\u003emodel(fruField);\n\t\t\tbreak;\n\t\tcase PLDM_FRU_FIELD_TYPE_PN:\n\t\t\tinitFruDecoratorIfNotExist();\n\t\t\tfruDecoratorsIntf-\u003epartNumber(fruField);\n\t\t\tbreak;\n\t\tcase PLDM_FRU_FIELD_TYPE_SN:\n\t\t\tinitFruDecoratorIfNotExist();\n\t\t\tfruDecoratorsIntf-\u003eserialNumber(fruField);\n\t\t\tbreak;\n```",
      "revId": "7c9c59d59057c488636996a7f7df026c695ff3f4",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
